vulnerabilities.title: Withdrawn: Code execution via SVG file upload in tiddlywiki
vulnerabilities.description:
## Withdrawn Advisory
This advisory has been withdrawn because it has been found to not be valid. Please see the issue [here](https://github.com/Jermolene/TiddlyWiki5/issues/7384) for more information.

## Original Description

An arbitrary file upload vulnerability in the file upload module of Tiddlywiki5 v5.2.2 allows attackers to execute arbitrary code via a crafted SVG file.
